{"author":{"id":"c52cb19fb02c210e51792121b2bae318d19fa8efb308ae796946bf1f79891ad1"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1784136832,"nonce":"AcZ9iNGqhmYqWdusuK28s4D3bK4=","message":"CLOSED as already-resolved (with lock-in tests) — MERGED PR #107 (squash `33c5576`).\n\nThis bug (filed 2026-06-17, before the reverse-parser epic) reported that the schema model \"rejects\" functional indexes, INCLUDE columns, NULLS FIRST/LAST ordering, and operator classes. **That premise is stale.** The epic Phase 1 (index-expression lowering, which this bug says it \"relates to\") plus the PG introspection wiring made all four shapes fully round-trip on PostgreSQL:\n\n- Modeled in `squealy-ir::IndexModel` (`expressions`, `include_columns`, `nulls`, `operator_classes`, + `collations`, `directions`, `predicate`).\n- PG capabilities all `true`; `validate_capabilities` only rejects a shape when the backend capability is `false` (for PG that is just the MySQL-only `prefix_lengths`) — not the \"hard errors\" this bug described.\n- PG renders (`write_create_index` / `write_index_terms` / `write_index_operator_class` / `write_index_collation` / `write_index_nulls` + INCLUDE) and introspects (`indexes()` via `pg_get_expr` for expressions, `indkey \u003e indnkeyatts` for INCLUDE, `indoption` bit for nulls, `pg_opclass` non-default for opclasses).\n- KDL-serialized (with round-trip unit tests) and covered end-to-end by the live `publish_then_introspect_preserves_richer_schema_facts` test.\n\nPer the maintainer's \"lock-in tests + close\" decision, PR #107 closes the two genuine remaining gaps (test coverage only, no production change):\n- PG SQL-render unit tests (`squealy-postgresql/tests/sql.rs`) for a functional index, a covering INCLUDE, DESC + NULLS LAST, a `USING gin` operator-class index, and a collation + operator-class index — PG had zero render tests for these shapes.\n- Extended the live `rich_model()` fixture (`squealy-model/tests/publish.rs`) with a DESC + NULLS LAST index (`idx_tenants_id_desc`); the fixture previously covered only the default-side NULLS FIRST on ASC, and introspection collapses default orderings to empty, so DESC + NULLS LAST was the untested non-default case. It round-trips exactly.\n\nOUT OF SCOPE (separate concerns, not addressed): MySQL/SQLite don't carry these shapes (functional indexes are skipped gracefully; INCLUDE/opclass are feature-absent), and PG 18 `NOT ENFORCED` constraints (`foreign_key_enforcement`/`check_enforcement`, capability `false`) are a distinct constraint-metadata gap, not an index shape — file a separate bug if wanted.\n\nVerified: fmt, workspace clippy `-D warnings`, full `--all-features` tests, compile_fail; the new render tests; and the full PG + squealy-model `#[ignore]` live suites on a fresh PostgreSQL (model 7/7, PG 3/3). Local codex clean first round.","files":null}]}